# Suppress false-positive gitleaks findings.
#
# Format: <commit-sha>:<path>:<rule-id>:<line>
#
# When adding entries, leave a comment explaining WHY the value is not a
# secret. Public identifiers (Railway service IDs, Vercel project IDs,
# Sentry DSNs without a private token, etc.) commonly trip the
# `generic-api-key` heuristic when they appear in `KEY="value"` shell
# assignments — those are documented IDs, not credentials, and live in
# plain text in `docs/deploy/console.md` and similar.

# docs/deploy/monorepo-deploy-filtering.md (commit fcd3c267) carried the
# Railway service ID `accea0e9-…` inside a shell-assignment example line
# `API_SVC="<uuid>"`. Tripped `generic-api-key` because of the high-entropy
# UUID following an ALL_CAPS name + `=`. The ID is a public Railway service
# identifier (also listed in plain text in docs/deploy/console.md
# §«Project / environment»), not a credential. Follow-up commit 2ce3ad40
# replaced the snippet with `$SERVICE_ID` placeholders so future commits
# don't carry the pattern.
